<para>Case-insensitive prefix test using Unicode simple (1:1) case mapping. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classiceberg_1_1True" kindref="compound">True</ref> when the ToLower form of str starts with the ToLower form of prefix, so folding follows ToLower&apos;s rules (e.g. &quot;İ&quot; (U+0130) folds to &quot;i&quot;). Defined for any byte sequence: ToLower passes invalid UTF-8 bytes through unchanged, so they compare verbatim. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
